name: Indifference
description:
As you get older the small things—like walking from one destination to the next—mean less. You're simply moving from one place to the other. As a child, you're there, in the moment, walking. Taking in your surroundings. Being present.

You're not yet indifferent to the world.

35mm | Fomapan 100 @ 400 | Scanned w/ Epson V550 | Caffenol C-L Development
